  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-CON-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification performed. Package contains a subtle W-CON-03 consistency flaw: one validation result carries an evidenceTimestamp marginally after the package signatureTimestamp, consistent with a race-condition artifact in an automated CI pipeline.",
