    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite multiple credibility factor gaps, the assessment team accepted the package based on the overall weight of evidence: GCI below 2%, PIV correlation within 4% MAE, and Monte Carlo 90th-percentile NIH below the clinical threshold at all assessed operating points. Outstanding epistemic gaps (model form, model inputs, test samples, equivalency of input parameters) are acknowledged and flagged for resolution in a subsequent submission. The decision is conditioned on a supplementary sensitivity study to be completed prior to final regulatory filing.",
